screen.texte: Welcome to the second scene
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap;                                     word-wrap: break-word;                                    color: white;                                    font-size: 16px;                                    margin: 0px;                                    font-family: Arial;                                    z-index: 102; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 29.4748%; top: 35.468%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 37.2454%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
It was supposed to be an epic space-opera in 3D animation

that explains how to connect to our network.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 7px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 103; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 9.53912%; top: 32.3153%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 84.2444%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
We used a respectable animation software, 

but the results were terrible.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 12.8617%; top: 36.7488%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 75.0268%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
So we decided to ditch it - 

it was too low-key even for our lo-fi taste.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap;                                     word-wrap: break-word;                                    color: white;                                    font-size: 16px;                                    margin: 0px;                                    font-family: Arial;                                    z-index: 102; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 22.6688%; top: 34.7783%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 52.4116%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
Which is really a pity, 

because the idea was great.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap;                                     word-wrap: break-word;                                    color: white;                                    font-size: 16px;                                    margin: 0px;                                    font-family: Arial;                                    z-index: 102; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 27.7063%; top: 34.9754%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 38.0493%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
It features Barbara as the only inhabitant of a comet travelling through space,

eating pizza and contemplating storytelling
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 103; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 9; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 24.0086%; top: 33.1034%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 50.8895%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
She encounters various characters and objects from many different stories,

all floating around her, like space debris
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 21.7694%; top: 32.3501%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 54.716%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: Here are some good stills, just to give you an idea:
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap;                                     word-wrap: break-word;                                    color: white;                                    font-size: 16px;                                    margin: 0px;                                    font-family: Arial;                                    z-index: 102; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 26.313%; top: 32.9064%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 43.9979%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: Then Batman comes and tells you to connect to Wi-Fi called “SCREENAGERS”
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 9; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 16.8901%; top: 35.49%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 69.2926%; height: auto; user-select: none;

white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 9; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 102; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 16.881%; top: 29.9507%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 69.2926%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
While you connect to wifi,

Barbara is counting the stars
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 9; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 25.134%; top: 35.665%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 45.1233%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
Then there is a cosmic storm during which she screams about 

how exciting it is to find herself in a place not covered by Google maps
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 103; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 22.0375%; top: 33.3016%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 54.1265%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
After the storm calms down, 

she tells you to open your Chrome / Safari / Firefox etc, 

and enter : futur.pizza

in your address bar.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 9; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 104; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 14.7453%; top: 19.7907%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 71.1147%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
Address bar - NOT search bar!

And while you’re trying to figure out the difference between the two,

she practices her ukulele
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 101; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 20.2681%; top: 19.6955%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 57.2883%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: This peaceful moment is than brutally interrupted
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 9; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 24.2765%; top: 38.0296%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 47.5884%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: Because the asteroid is suddenly torched by a passing dragon
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 103; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 9; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 25.9914%; top: 35.665%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 43.462%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: and everything dissolves into white nothingness
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; font-family: Arial; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 9; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 18.5423%; top: 37.6355%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 58.5209%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
I am a hero in a play. It's a kind of lo-fi space-opera, in which I fight against my own monsters using a bombastic red keyboard hung around the neck like in the heyday of 80s synth-pop.
How does it end?
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 55px; font-family: fixedsys; z-index: 101; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 13.8874%; top: 31.0181%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 73.9807%; height: auto; user-select: none;

white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 55px; margin: 0px; font-family: fixedsys; z-index: 102; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 34.1372%; top: 42.4631%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 32.7974%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: Theatre directors want their play to end with a gripping monologue, like that of Charlie Chaplin at the end of The Great Dictator. How could this monologue begin?
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 55px; font-family: fixedsys; z-index: 9; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 14.6917%; top: 32.255%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 73.9807%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
I’m not afraid of the dark any more.
Things like this happen all the time.
I also have a fear of not having water.
So, as a precaution, I put in aluminium, but I'm not sure it really helps…”
Then other characters came on stage, and there was a lot of interaction and interaction. But it was too complicated. 
So a machine by the name James Joyce wrote a play called Ulysses.
It was a little better.
The end.
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 45px; margin: 0px; font-family: fixedsys;z-index: 105; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 12.2186%; top: 21.0837%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 77.7599%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte: Theatre directors want their play to end with an epic song, in magic realism style. How to make this happen?
screen.style: white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: white; font-size: 55px; font-family: fixedsys; z-index: 101; text-align: center; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: none;z-index: 101; text-align: center; position: absolute; left: 14.7453%; top: 35.49%; box-sizing: border-box; width: 73.9807%; height: auto; user-select: none;

screen.texte:
An asteroid hits the stage, absorbing everything into a black hole.  Spectators stay glued to their seats for days, watching the hole waiting for something to happen. It is a wonderful visual spectacle. But the end is not the only end. 
Spectators organise into a union. One of them sings: “Let's all get on stage and have a good old time”
